				                <div>Hello Mark,<br />
<br />
Thank you for your question. It seems to be a common problem, judging by the amount of search results.<br />
<br />
I found the following <a href="http://logorrhoea.net/2014/01/how-to-block-semalt-com-referrer-traffic-using-htaccess/" target="_blank" >solution</a> via online search, where it is blocked by referrer:<br />
<br />
<pre># block visitors referred from semalt.com<br />
RewriteEngine on<br />
RewriteCond %{HTTP_REFERER} semalt\.com [NC]<br />
RewriteRule .* - [F]</pre><br />
<br />
If you have any further questions, feel free to post them below.<br />
Thank you,<br />
